  "text": "Respiration of an organism is an important attribute of its physiological activity and reflects the metabolism in vivo. It is known that during insect diapause oxygen consumption is low. While the information on the physiological differences between the diapause and subitaneous embryos of copepods is lacking, even though it has generally been assumed to be comparable to that in insects [CITATION_1] .",
